This paper deals with the design of wireless information and power transfer in multiuser OFDM systems, which involves topics related to information theory, networking, system engineering, multimedia, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which focuses on the mathematical foundations of information and communication. The second likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), which deals with the design, implementation, and evaluation of computer networks and protocols. The third likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which studies the modeling, analysis, and control of complex systems. The fourth likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia), which covers the processing, coding, and transmission of multimedia data. The fifth likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the development of algorithms and models that enable computers to learn from data.
